<p><strong>Short Spear</strong>&nbsp;is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spears" href="/Spears" target="">Spear</a>&nbsp;in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. The <strong>Short Spear</strong>&nbsp;scales primarily with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Strength" href="/Strength" target="">Strength</a>&nbsp;and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dexterity" href="/Dexterity" target="">Dexterity</a>&nbsp;and is a good <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Weapons" href="/Weapons" target="">Weapon</a> for short range melee combat.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>An exceedingly plain spear of modest weight.</em></p> 
 <p><em>Simple to wield compared to many of its peers, its strong attack unleashes a series of successive piercing thrusts.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to Find Short Spear in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Short Spear weapon can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Starting Equipment for the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Prophet" href="/Prophet" target="">Prophet</a> Class.</li> 
 <li>Can be purchased from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Twin Maiden Husks" href="/Twin+Maiden+Husks" target="">Twin Maiden Husks</a>&nbsp;at the&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Roundtable Hold" href="/Roundtable+Hold" target="">Roundtable Hold</a>&nbsp;for&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/runes-currency-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="runes currency elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;600&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes" target="">Runes</a>.</li> 
 <li>Drops from <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Godrick Foot Soldier" href="/Godrick+Foot+Soldier">Godrick</a>, <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Radahn Foot Soldier" href="/Radahn+Foot+Soldier">Radahn</a>, and <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Leyndell Foot Soldier" href="/Leyndell+Foot+Soldier">Leyndell Foot Soldiers</a>.</li> 
 <li>The footsoldiers who wield this weapon have a chance to drop it. Agheel lake north's sight of grace is probably the closest one to a group of godrick footmen with the short spear near the bridge.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring Short Spear Notes &amp; Tips</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Weapon <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Skills" href="/Skills" target="">Skill</a>:&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Impaling Thrust" href="/Impaling+Thrust" target="">Impaling Thrust</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon can be infused with&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>.</li> 
 <li><strong>Short Spear</strong> can be upgraded by using <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Smithing Stones" href="/Smithing+Stones" target="">Smithing Stones</a></li> 
 <li>This weapon has a special R2, shared by the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Cleanrot Spear" href="/Cleanrot+Spear">Cleanrot Spear</a>.</li> 
 <li>Sell Value:&nbsp;&nbsp;<img title="Runes" src="/file/Elden-Ring/er-runes-13.png" alt="er runes 13" width="18" height="18">&nbsp;100 <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Runes" href="/Runes">Runes</a></li> 
 <li>Other notes and player tips go here</li> 
</ul> 
<p>The Short Spear can be infused with <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Ashes of War" href="/Ashes+of+War" target="">Ashes of War</a>. Click below for a list of all possible Ashes of War that can be applied to the spear weapon.</p> 
