				<li id="16777918" class="cmnt-root" data="0" data-d="1663906713000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578255/Short-Spear" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">23 Sep 2022 00:18</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16777918" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Ok, so I have been playing around with the short spear for the past few days, and I think I finally have it pegged at what niche it fills. On paper, it&apos;s the most vanilla of the spears (and rightfully so), but it does fulfill some very interesting synergies provided you build for it correctly. Let&apos;s go with the obvious: it&apos;s one of the few weapons that actually can use the blue dancer charm and benefit from it. Assuming your character is completely naked, you can stack up: winged sword insignia, blue dancer charm, spear talisman, and even radagon&apos;s soreseal and that would put you at 7.6 equipment load, right under the first softcap for the BDC. That&apos;s a very solid loadout on it&apos;s own, and although this would mean you would be naked, would have great use for SL1 runs to maximize damage.<br/><br/>The other fact, as alluded above, is that the requirements are SL1 friendly. it only requires 10/10. easy peasy. it&apos;s also a spear, so it has all the perks that comes with. The shortspear does lack a normal sweep like the partisan, but this can be alleviated fairly easy by kitting it with an AoW  that is either A) a sweep or B) some form of other crowd control, like a spin.<br/><br/>Not the best for damage. There are stronger options out there but the scaling is pretty nice. All of that is just one example. In short, it&apos;s a good weapon, with unique circumstances to allow it to shine. don&apos;t pass up on it.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16777918" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16777918" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>0</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="zz-16777918"><div class="ng-scope"><textarea id="dcomment" class="ng-pristine ng-untouched ng-invalid ng-invalid-required" placeholder="Input your comments:"></textarea><button id="btn-16777918" class="btn btn-default btnPostReply"><i class="glyphicon glyphicon-pencil"></i> Submit</button><img id="newCommentAvatar" src="/images/avatar.png"/></div></div></div></div><div class="clearfix"></div><ul class="children collapse" id="replies-16777918"></ul></li></ul></li>
			
